Notes: A large tussock-forming, wiry clump (likely Juncus roemerianus) occupies the majority of the quadrat; remaining green wiry/matted grass interpreted as Spartina patens. Some dead old material around the base and a small bare area are visible. No shell counts or clear crab burrows observed.

Quadrat dominated by a fine, wiry, matted tussock consistent with Spartina patens (~75%). Central dark area and exposed tussock base counted as bare ground (~10%) and dead organic material from dried blades/roots (~15%). No oysters, mussels, periwinkles, or obvious crab burrows visible. Confidence high for S. patens ID due to blade texture and hummock form; moderate for exact area estimates.
